Text.Value: How do I get to meet the Absolute?
Please Z'rell, and you will be called to ascend to the tower-top. Many have gone before you.
How about a dance?
*Soft hoot.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gnoll tilts its head and nods.
EditorData.NodeContext: Gnolls make hyena noises - this is a soft sound of acknowledgement/comprehension. Tilting its head and nodding.

Text.Value: Put aside dreams of mincing her. Help her take back control.
Now... Barnabus, darling... NO!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Hands up, ready to back away
EditorData.NodeContext: Cautious, suddenly standing in front of a wild animal let loose from the leash. Last line is a shout as gnoll jumps on her.

Text.Value: Their will has always been Hers to command. I am simply putting it back where it belongs. Behold:
Leave.
Gnolls are beasts, plain and simple.
Here. I meant this as a treat for Barnabus, but he doesn't deserve it now.
You've actually stood before the Absolute?
If you return at all.
Hah. For all the power She lends us... I am still only an imperfect vessel.

EditorData.NodeContext: Panting, wry but relieved at a near miss

Text.Value: Oh? As you wish.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: She releases the gnoll from her thrall with a gesture

Text.Value: Aw - you'd like that, wouldn't you, Barnabus?
Reinforce her efforts with your own.
He isn't the first to die. Her love is simply too much for some. I hope you will fare better, when your time comes.
...M... any... heaaarts... one... soul...

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: in obvious pain at human speech

Text.Value: What would you like him to do?
Go on now, friend. It seems I must have a stern chat with Barnabus.

EditorData.NodeContext: Bad things lie ahead for Barnabus
EditorData.logicalname: HasMet, saw power, gnoll didn't die

Text.Value: You use a spoon to stir the soup, Barnabus. Forget the axe, my darling.

EditorData.NodeContext: Kindly - speaking to a favourite child that is none too bright

Text.Value: Compel the gnolls to pulp their master.
Sever her control once and for all.
A moment, True Soul.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mid-conversation with a gnoll, holds up hand to us as we approach

Text.Value: *You feel her will surge outwards and envelop the creature, inexorable as the tide.*
Yes? Barnabus and the boys get antsy if I'm distracted for too long.
Nothing. Keep your sick games to yourself.
A little advice - should you seek an audience with Her, steel yourself.
I have. It is one thing to hear Her voice. Quite another to feel the power She can grant. Observe:
Hah. For all the power She lends us... I am still only an imperfect vessel. You will fare better when your time comes, I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: Panting, wry but relieved at a near miss

Text.Value: I've shown Barnabus a kinder way. A kinder name is only fitting.
You decide.
Leave.
Praise Her works - committed by the hands of Her faithful. Observe:
Soft and sweet as pudding, isn't he? He no longer remembers his life in the wild.
...The prayer, I think. Barnabus struggles with civilised speech, but he's been practising.
You ascend the tower as a True Soul, and return as something more.
'Barnabus'...?
This gift you mentioned. I'd like to see it after all.
NO, Barnabus! We talked about this.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind-meld VFX flares again as she redoubles her effort, straining

Text.Value: *The weight of the assault drives the gnoll to his knees, defiance melting away like snow in summer.*
Oh, Barnabus. I'm so sorry, my darling.

EditorData.NodeContext: Disappointed and sad - but nothing to be done about it

Text.Value: I've never seen a tame gnoll before.
She gathers many threads for Her Design - but it is still Her Design. And Barnabus has found his place in it. Observe:
*They battle silently for a long moment, the gnoll's heart drumming with strain. Then all at once, his heart stops.*
To be remade, we must be willing to suffer.
That is the gift the Absolute gave me, when I stood before Her. To rewrite the lives of Her faithful - make them believe they are something better.
You mean you enslave people.
*Growl.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Gnoll pauses, shakes off the control for a brief moment
EditorData.NodeContext: Low growl as it comes back to its senses. Gnoll pauses, shakes off the control for a brief moment
EditorData.SFXTags: Barnabus growling sound to break free of mindmeld

Text.Value: Heart-warming. Praise Her name.
I thought the Absolute accepted us all as we are.
*Whine.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The gnoll begins a pathetic, shuffling dance on the spot. Think a wild bear forced to dance in the circus.
EditorData.NodeContext: A soft hyena whine - The gnoll begins a pathetic, shuffling dance on the spot. Think a wild bear forced to dance in the circus.

Text.Value: Now! How can I help you?
Barnabus, sweetie! Come show what a good boy you are.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Gnoll] transition from normal idle to stand at attention idle <GREG>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind-meld effect / voice reverberation. The gnoll stands to rigid attention, enthralled.
EditorData.SFXTags: Barnabus whines when put under spell/Mindmeld SFX

Text.Value: Though not all have returned.
*Like rope drawn taut beneath the blade, the connection simply... snaps.*

EditorData.SFXTags: Mindmeld sfx/ Barnabus growl and roar when he break free

Text.Value: You'll do well when you meet with the Absolute, I think.

EditorData.NodeContext: Appraising, seeing us with new eyes

Text.Value: Oh, the good is buried deeper in some, that is true. But She will always find it.
Ughhh.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Barnabus keels over out of shot, dead.

Text.Value: It seems you're not as commanding as you think.
You almost make this audience sound dangerous.

Synopsis: A True Soul oversees some gnolls in the kitchen. They're uncharacteristically quiet, and she explains that the Absolute has given her the ability to 'bring out the good' in then. In truth she is simply dominating them - she'll demonstrate by forcing the gnoll to perform tricks, but we can subvert her power and let the gnoll kill her.
